              <h4 class="section-title">About the Museum &amp; Archives</h4>

              <!-- Move to WP -->
              <p>The Cumberland Museum and Archives opened its doors in 1981 and is home to the extensive archives and artifacts of the community of Cumberland. We are open year round and offer over 40 exhibits, a Company Store, research services, after school programs, heritage events, guided tours, films and a replica coal mine.  </p>

              <p>Christmas Hours: Closed December&nbsp;24-26 and December&nbsp;30 – November&nbsp;1<br>
              Winter Hours (September 13 to May 31): 10am to 5pm – Wednesday to Sunday<br>
                Summer Hours (June 1 to September 12): 10am to 5pm – 7 days a week<br>
                Closed on statutory holidays and Easter Sunday
              </p>
